--- a/README.md
+++ b/README.md
@@ -1,25 +1,42 @@
+# Tensura: Primordial Authority
-Installation information
-=======
+NeoForge 1.21.1 addon project for learning Tensura Reincarnated / ManasCore modding.
-This template repository can be directly cloned to get you started with a new
-mod. Simply create a new repository cloned from this one, by following the
-instructions provided by [GitHub](https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/creating-and-managing-repositories/creating-a-repository-from-a-template).
+## Template entry points
-Once you have your clone, simply open the repository in the IDE of your choice. The usual recommendation for an IDE is either IntelliJ IDEA or Eclipse.
+- `src/main/java/com/ragnar/primordialauthority/registry/AuthorityTemplateRegistry.java`
+- `src/main/java/com/ragnar/primordialauthority/registry/AuthoritySkills.java`
+- `src/main/java/com/ragnar/primordialauthority/registry/AuthorityRaces.java`
+- `src/main/java/com/ragnar/primordialauthority/registry/AuthorityEffects.java`
+- `src/main/java/com/ragnar/primordialauthority/registry/AuthorityConfigs.java`
+- `src/main/java/com/ragnar/primordialauthority/registry/AuthorityZones.java`

-If at any point you are missing libraries in your IDE, or you've run into problems you can
-run `gradlew --refresh-dependencies` to refresh the local cache. `gradlew clean` to reset everything
-{this does not affect your code} and then start the process again.
+## Example templates

-Mapping Names:
-============
-By default, the MDK is configured to use the official mapping names from Mojang for methods and fields
-in the Minecraft codebase. These names are covered by a specific license. All modders should be aware of this
-license. For the latest license text, refer to the mapping file itself, or the reference copy here:
-https://github.com/NeoForged/NeoForm/blob/main/Mojang.md
+The example files use `.java.example` so the project can still compile before
+Tensura/ManasCore jars are installed and before you are ready to activate a system.

-Additional Resources:
-==========
-Community Documentation: https://docs.neoforged.net/
-NeoForged Discord: https://discord.neoforged.net/
+- `skill/ExampleBasicSkill.java.example`
+- `skill/progression/*.java.example`
+- `skill/unique/*.java.example`
+- `skill/ultimate/*.java.example`
+- `race/ExampleBasicRace.java.example`
+- `effect/ExampleBasicEffect.java.example`
+- `config/ExampleCommonConfig.java.example`
+- `zone/*.java.example`
+
+## Suggested learning order
+
+1. Copy one `.java.example` file to `.java`.
+2. Register it in the matching `Authority*` registry class.
+3. Build and test before copying the next template.
+4. Keep each mechanic small until it works in game.
+
+## Dependencies
+
+Put local Tensura Reincarnated, ManasCore, and optional integration jars in `libs/`.
+
+## Resource guide
+
+See `docs/resources-template.md` for notes about language keys, tags, recipes,
+loot tables, textures, and models.
